# Changelog

All notable changes to WiFi Refresh Utility are documented here.

## [0.3.0] - 2026-06-30

### Changed
- **MAJOR: Replaced C# toast helper with BurntToast module**
  - Eliminates complex COM interop code and `WScript.Shell` AUMID registration bug
  - BurntToast handles AUMID registration internally (properly uses `IPropertyStore`)
  - Reduces maintenance burden and external dependencies
  - Notification system now more reliable across Windows versions

### Removed
- `Build-ToastHelper()` PowerShell function (no longer needed)
- `$toastHelperProject`, `$toastHelperExe`, `$publishFolder` variables
- Dependency on compiled C# helper executable
- Manual Start Menu shortcut creation logic (BurntToast handles it)

### Fixed
- Toast notifications silently failing due to improper AUMID registration
- No longer requires dotnet CLI to build/deploy
- Removed the "succeeds with exit code 0 but shows no notification" failure mode

### Notes
- Legacy `ToastNotificationHelper.csproj` and `toastnotificationhelper.cs` kept for reference only
- BurntToast module auto-installs on first run (requires internet for NuGet download)
- Tested on Windows 10 build 19045

## [0.2.5] - 2026-06-29

### Features
- C# toast helper with manual AUMID registration via `WScript.Shell`
- PowerShell backend with DNS/ARP flushing
- AutoHotkey tray menu launcher
- Notification toggle via ini config

### Known Issues
- ⚠️ AUMID registration silently fails (`WScript.Shell` doesn't expose `AppUserModelID` property)
- Toast notifications appear in notification settings but don't display as banners
- Requires `dotnet` CLI for building the C# helper on first run

---

## Migration Guide (0.2.5 → 0.3.0)

### For Users

1. Update `wifi-refresh.ps1` from this repo
2. No other changes needed — just drop it in place
3. Delete `publish/` folder if you want to clean up (no longer used)
4. First run will auto-install BurntToast module (one-time)

### For Developers

- Remove any custom `Build-ToastHelper` calls
- Stop referencing `$toastHelperExe` or the compiled helper
- BurntToast is now the single source of truth for notifications
- To customize notification appearance, edit BurntToast parameters in `Show-Notification`

---